00:14:14,848 --> 00:14:18,231
Killing somebody has a way
of throwing a man off-track.

254
00:14:18,231 --> 00:14:19,788
Not for Tommy Sugar.

255
00:14:19,788 --> 00:14:23,321
He's been Phily's top boxing
promoter the last 25 years.

256
00:14:23,321 --> 00:14:25,926
Well that's some truth,
and here's some more:

257
00:14:25,926 --> 00:14:27,807
The night Jerry Stone died,

258
00:14:27,807 --> 00:14:30,543
Tommy Sugar was born.

259
00:14:43,518 --> 00:14:46,883
It was 1976. The bicentennial.

260
00:14:46,883 --> 00:14:50,062
And 'Rocky' was
as American as it gets.

261
00:14:50,062 --> 00:14:52,076
And you saw a way to exploit that.

262
00:14:52,076 --> 00:14:53,600
Saw opportunity.

263
00:14:53,600 --> 00:14:54,726
For one and all.

264
00:14:54,726 --> 00:14:56,902
That kind of timing don't come twice.

265
00:14:56,902 --> 00:14:59,022
So the pressure was on.

266
00:14:59,022 --> 00:15:01,255
- This fight had to live up.
- No doubt.

267
00:15:01,255 --> 00:15:04,219
One thing for an underdog to go
15 rounds on the silver screen,

268
00:15:04,219 --> 00:15:07,179
another to make that
happen in real life.

269
00:15:07,179 --> 00:15:09,985
I tribute to the young man who fought.

270
00:15:09,985 --> 00:15:12,552
And you did nothing to help it along?

271
00:15:13,737 --> 00:15:15,284
Like what?

272
00:15:15,284 --> 00:15:17,049
Jerry would bleed a lot.

273
00:15:17,049 --> 00:15:18,385
Which was a good thing, right?

274
00:15:18,385 --> 00:15:20,140
But if you were trying to
remake 'Rocky',

275
00:15:20,140 --> 00:15:22,352
you need Jerry to go 15 rounds.

276
00:15:22,352 --> 00:15:24,348
So you don't want too
much of a good thing.

277
00:15:24,348 --> 00:15:27,767
So maybe as insurance you paid
the referee to keep it going.

278
00:15:27,767 --> 00:15:29,483
No matter what.

279
00:15:29,483 --> 00:15:31,541
Well, Sonny took a deal like that?

280
00:15:31,541 --> 00:15:32,442
Yep.

281
00:15:32,442 --> 00:15:36,473
Ha, ha, ha- I wish I'd known
he was open for business.

282
00:15:36,473 --> 00:15:40,680
You know, where you ought to
be looking is the C.Y.O.

283
00:15:40,680 --> 00:15:42,815
Catholic Youth Organization.

284
00:15:42,815 --> 00:15:44,771
Where I plucked Jerry from.

285
00:15:44,771 --> 00:15:46,540
A half a dozen fighters
came to me

286
00:15:46,540 --> 00:15:48,578
crying the blues
after being overlooked.

287
00:15:48,578 --> 00:15:51,010
So one of these sore losers
from the C.Y.O.

288
00:15:51,010 --> 00:15:55,700
pays Sonny 1,500 dollars to see
Jerry take the beating of his life?

289
00:15:55,700 --> 00:15:59,707
Your best fighters,
always hold a grudge.

290
00:16:07,220 --> 00:16:09,810
The C.Y.O. was 
at it's height in the 70's.

291
00:16:09,810 --> 00:16:13,855
Instead of a kid sucking on cigarettes
all day long he had a place to go.

292
00:16:13,855 --> 00:16:16,702
And Jerry Stone participated
in the boxing program?

293
00:16:16,702 --> 00:16:19,344
Jerry would serve mass for me
on Sunday mornings

294
00:16:19,344 --> 00:16:21,115
and then fight for me
on Sunday nights.

295
00:16:21,115 --> 00:16:23,926
Which eventually lands him
this bout with Mo.

296
00:16:23,926 --> 00:16:25,134
Right.

297
00:16:25,134 --> 00:16:27,879
Heard not everyone was
overjoyed by that.

298
00:16:27,879 --> 00:16:29,281
You gotta be remembered that

299
00:16:29,281 --> 00:16:31,852
these kids had their noses
pressed right up against it.

300
00:16:31,852 --> 00:16:33,547
And along comes Jerry,

301
00:16:33,547 --> 00:16:36,884
He's got a chance
at a real professional fight.

302
00:16:36,884 --> 00:16:40,395
Anyone so jealous they might wanna
see real harm come to Jerry?

303
00:16:40,395 --> 00:16:42,604
Pay the ref off to see that happen?

304
00:16:42,604 --> 00:16:45,531
Ah, deep down, these guys
knew they were not better than Jerry.

305
00:16:45,531 --> 00:16:47,856
Just a bunch of ham and eggers.

306
00:16:47,856 --> 00:16:50,340
- Except, uh- one of 'em, I guess.

307
00:16:50,340 --> 00:16:51,174
- Who?

308
00:16:51,174 --> 00:16:53,354
Bucky Lowsen
Best fighter we had.

309
00:16:53,354 --> 00:16:54,594
Better than Jerry?

310
00:16:54,594 --> 00:16:57,179
They wanted more of an underdog.
He had too good a record.

311
00:16:57,179 --> 00:16:58,911
And how'd he deal with that?

312
00:16:58,911 --> 00:17:00,680
Bucky didn't like coming
in second to Jerry

313
00:17:00,680 --> 00:17:03,238
that seem to be happening quite a lot.

314
00:17:03,815 --> 00:17:07,234
♪ Marshall Tucker Band 
"Can't You See" ♪

315
00:17:07,234 --> 00:17:08,040
Hey.

316
00:17:08,040 --> 00:17:10,035
Can I borrow the key 
to the gym, father?

317
00:17:10,035 --> 00:17:12,277
I want to work the bags a little.

318
00:17:13,576 --> 00:17:15,452
Mr. Carroll.

319
00:17:16,206 --> 00:17:18,944
Must think Rome was built in a day.

320
00:17:19,637 --> 00:17:21,540
Hey, go play some records.

321
00:17:21,540 --> 00:17:23,813
I'll be right over.

322
00:17:24,280 --> 00:17:26,098
You just won't give him a chance,
will you?

323
00:17:26,098 --> 00:17:27,214
Why should I?

324
00:17:27,214 --> 00:17:28,930
A bum is a bum is a bum.

325
00:17:28,930 --> 00:17:29,850
Hey.

326
00:17:30,071 --> 00:17:31,561
Hey, I've looking for you.

327
00:17:31,561 --> 00:17:33,307
Buck. / Don't 'Buck' me boy!

328
00:17:33,307 --> 00:17:34,496
You get the message I left you?

329
00:17:34,496 --> 00:17:36,723
Look, Buck.
This is Mr. Sugar's fight.

330
00:17:36,723 --> 00:17:38,572
- You should talk to him.
- I did.

331
00:17:38,572 --> 00:17:41,677
My only way in that ring is
if you were out.

332
00:17:41,677 --> 00:17:44,830
I'm sorry. I'm staying put.

333
00:17:44,830 --> 00:17:47,375
- Hey, sucker, we ain't through here.
- Buck, Buck, back off.

334
00:17:47,375 --> 00:17:50,256
You want to start
a donnybrook, start with me.

335
00:17:52,786 --> 00:17:54,136
Fine.

336
00:17:56,983 --> 00:17:58,595
Hey, Sonny.

337
00:17:58,977 --> 00:18:01,167
You seen Jimmy the jeweler lately?

338
00:18:01,167 --> 00:18:02,750
What are you talking about?

339
00:18:02,750 --> 00:18:05,949
Jerry purchased a fancy
engagement ring.

340
00:18:05,949 --> 00:18:07,720
Seems to think he's marrying Gina.

341
00:18:07,720 --> 00:18:09,596
Bucky, give it a rest.

342
00:18:09,596 --> 00:18:12,682
Maybe you fighting Mo
ain't such a bad thing.

343
00:18:12,682 --> 00:18:14,500
After he puts you in a coma,

344
00:18:14,500 --> 00:18:18,926
guess whose brawny shoulder's
gonna be there for Gina to cry on.

345
00:18:24,403 --> 00:18:26,651
So, Buck and Gina had history.

346
00:18:26,651 --> 00:18:28,381
Sweethearts. / In high school?

347
00:18:28,381 --> 00:18:29,492
Elementary.

348
00:18:29,492 --> 00:18:32,073
He'd been carrying a torch
for her since the fifth grade.

349
00:18:32,073 --> 00:18:33,445
How do you know that?

350
00:18:33,445 --> 00:18:37,177
Well, around here if you don't get the
story on some kid after the mass?

351
00:18:37,177 --> 00:18:39,786
You believe your butt
you would at the bar.

352
00:18:39,786 --> 00:18:43,195
So between losing both the fight
and the girl to Jerry.

353
00:18:43,195 --> 00:18:45,677
Hmm, Buck was having a rough go.

354
00:18:49,293 --> 00:18:51,310
Alright Scotty, I'll see you then.

355
00:18:51,310 --> 00:18:52,407
Valens?

356
00:18:52,407 --> 00:18:54,201
Yeah. / He alright?

357
00:18:54,201 --> 00:18:55,713
We'er gonna grab some drinks.

358
00:18:55,713 --> 00:18:57,831
Good. Doing better than yesterday.

359
00:18:57,831 --> 00:18:58,998
You talked to him?

360
00:18:58,998 --> 00:19:00,481
Yeah.

361
00:19:00,749 --> 00:19:02,499
Buck Lowson's got a record.

362
00:19:02,499 --> 00:19:04,333
Two days before the fight,

363
00:19:04,333 --> 00:19:06,145
Buck robbed a convenient store.

364
00:19:06,145 --> 00:19:08,935
This says he was arrested in '78.
Not '76.

365
00:19:08,935 --> 00:19:10,542
It took that long to catch him.

366
00:19:10,542 --> 00:19:12,079
How much did Buck get away with?

367
00:19:12,079 --> 00:19:14,347
Two thousand and a thing
of peanut butter.

368
00:19:14,347 --> 00:19:16,456
And two whole years
to spread it around.

369
00:19:16,456 --> 00:19:20,376
Yeah. But maybe only took two days
before he burned all 1,500 of it.

370
00:19:20,376 --> 00:19:23,933
Right. Fifteen hundred.
Sonny's asking price.

371
00:19:29,879 --> 00:19:32,583
I don't know what you're talking about!

372
00:19:32,583 --> 00:19:35,609
Buck, I might even believe you
if not for the timing, I mean.

373
00:19:35,609 --> 00:19:37,303
You never stole anything else
in your life.

374
00:19:37,303 --> 00:19:38,753
That's the god's honest truth.

375
00:19:38,753 --> 00:19:41,873
- Nothing before that day or after.
- But that day is the problem, Buck.

376
00:19:41,873 --> 00:19:43,697
Because it was two days
before the fight.

377
00:19:43,697 --> 00:19:46,412
- How do you explain that?
- I can't.

378
00:19:46,412 --> 00:19:47,814
Start with the money.

379
00:19:47,814 --> 00:19:49,930
What d'you do with it?

380
00:19:50,310 --> 00:19:52,968
Buck, we know you wished Jerry ill.

381
00:19:52,968 --> 00:19:55,893
And that you and Gina go way back.

382
00:19:58,252 --> 00:19:59,533
Let him call a lawyer.

383
00:19:59,533 --> 00:20:01,892
I don' want a lawyer.
I can't afford one.

384
00:20:01,892 --> 00:20:04,749
Fine. I'll make sure
you get a PD.

385
00:20:04,749 --> 00:20:06,269
If you're lucky you might even
get a good one.

386
00:20:06,269 --> 00:20:08,185
You think a public defender's
gonna care about me?

387
00:20:08,185 --> 00:20:09,630
Alright, maybe not. But, Buck.

388
00:20:09,630 --> 00:20:12,261
If you're not gonna talk about the money,
what are we supposed to do?

389
00:20:12,261 --> 00:20:16,368
Besides, if you're so innocent,
what are you hedging for?

390
00:20:17,825 --> 00:20:20,255
Because I don't wanna hurt her.

391
00:20:20,737 --> 00:20:24,331
♪ Bachman Turner Overdrive 
"You Ain't Seen Nothing Yet" ♪

392
00:20:34,013 --> 00:20:35,511
Hey, Buck.

393
00:20:35,973 --> 00:20:37,982
- What are you doing here?
- Well, what are you doing here?

394
00:20:37,982 --> 00:20:39,513
I'm waiting for Jerry.

395
00:20:39,513 --> 00:20:41,141
He's running, too.

396
00:20:41,141 --> 00:20:44,825
Oh, so suddenly he's humping
early morning runs, huh? / Um-hmm.

397
00:20:44,825 --> 00:20:46,426
Priceless.

398
00:20:46,426 --> 00:20:49,519
Well, Buck. Here he is, so...

399
00:20:49,519 --> 00:20:52,785
Relax. He ain't gonna
see us. Look.

400
00:20:52,785 --> 00:20:55,237
Got his head in the clouds.

401
00:20:55,237 --> 00:20:57,165
What a clown.

402
00:20:57,438 --> 00:20:59,884
He could run these steps like Rocky
all day, it's gonna mean zip.

403
00:20:59,884 --> 00:21:03,528
No. He's been working real hard.

404
00:21:10,968 --> 00:21:13,651
Gina, the fix is in.

405
00:21:13,651 --> 00:21:14,733
What?

406
00:21:14,733 --> 00:21:18,095
Mo's taking a dive first round,
Jerry's gonna win.

407
00:21:19,653 --> 00:21:22,302
It won't be a real fight?

408
00:21:24,538 --> 00:21:27,104
That'll hurt Jerry real bad.

409
00:21:27,104 --> 00:21:29,059
Hey, there's nothing you can do about.

410
00:21:29,059 --> 00:21:30,601
Except take advantage.

411
00:21:30,601 --> 00:21:31,722
What do you mean?

412
00:21:31,722 --> 00:21:35,676
You know what the odds are for Jerry
winning in a first round knockout?

413
00:21:35,676 --> 00:21:38,997
What? / Twenty to one.

414
00:21:39,542 --> 00:21:42,636
That's why I ain't busting
Balboa's bubble just yet.

415
00:21:42,636 --> 00:21:45,760
There're some real dough
to be made first.

416
00:22:10,783 --> 00:22:13,242
Gina couldn't resist a sure thing.

417
00:22:13,242 --> 00:22:14,869
She was a gambler?

418
00:22:14,869 --> 00:22:17,911
I robbed that store
so I could get her betting money.

419
00:22:17,911 --> 00:22:19,677
Did you tell her how you got it?

420
00:22:19,677 --> 00:22:21,403
No. I wanted to impress her.

421
00:22:21,403 --> 00:22:23,745
Not tell her I was scum.

422
00:22:24,459 --> 00:22:26,554
Had it bad for her, huh, Buck?

423
00:22:26,554 --> 00:22:29,000
My whole stupid life.

424
00:22:29,000 --> 00:22:32,684
So Gina acts all broken up for Jerry
that the fight's gonna be a fake.

425
00:22:32,684 --> 00:22:34,964
But dries her eyes pretty quick.

426
00:22:34,964 --> 00:22:37,343
And places her own bet on it.

427
00:22:45,172 --> 00:22:46,286
Hey, boss.

428
00:22:46,286 --> 00:22:49,108
- Can I talk to you for a minute.
- Scotty, hey, sure.

429
00:22:50,268 --> 00:22:54,912
What happened in that interview
was 100% the wrong way.

430
00:22:54,912 --> 00:22:57,329
I mean, thumping on anybody.
Doesn't matter who.

431
00:22:57,329 --> 00:22:59,306
You can't do it.

432
00:22:59,892 --> 00:23:01,268
Okay.

433
00:23:01,268 --> 00:23:05,690
I assure you, it will not happen again.

434
00:23:05,690 --> 00:23:08,631
Well, that's good Scotty
'cause it can't.

435
00:23:10,736 --> 00:23:13,085
Anything else?

436
00:23:13,085 --> 00:23:19,520
Well, I was hoping the uh-,
suspension could be lifted...early.

437
00:23:19,520 --> 00:23:20,994
I didn't suspend you Scotty.

438
00:23:20,994 --> 00:23:24,831
I encouraged you to take time off.

439
00:23:25,058 --> 00:23:28,082
I'd like you to encourage me
to come back.

440
00:23:28,658 --> 00:23:30,516
How are you feeling?

441
00:23:30,516 --> 00:23:32,250
Great.

442
00:23:33,230 --> 00:23:34,640
Sorry, Scotty. I can't do it.

443
00:23:34,640 --> 00:23:36,565
What do you mean? Why?

444
00:23:37,268 --> 00:23:40,010
Well, I'll ask you again.
How are you feeling?

445
00:23:41,229 --> 00:23:43,194
I said fine.

446
00:23:43,697 --> 00:23:45,219
You're not ready yet.

447
00:23:45,219 --> 00:23:46,310
Boss...

448
00:23:46,310 --> 00:23:49,604
How do you feel, Scotty?

449
00:23:59,830 --> 00:24:02,977
Not...not that good.

450
00:24:04,351 --> 00:24:06,095
Hey.

451
00:24:07,178 --> 00:24:08,489
Come next week.

452
00:24:08,489 --> 00:24:10,882
We'll get you back on the job.

453
00:24:19,501 --> 00:24:22,327
I thought Jerry was your big love
of your life, Gina.

454
00:24:22,327 --> 00:24:23,393
He was.

455
00:24:23,393 --> 00:24:27,152
So why let him go ahead with the fight
you knew was rigged.

456
00:24:27,152 --> 00:24:30,186
'Cause you had money on that fight.

457
00:24:30,186 --> 00:24:31,943
Yeah, I did.

458
00:24:31,943 --> 00:24:35,808
You took the dough from Buck and
the twenty to one odds that came with it.

459
00:24:35,808 --> 00:24:38,245
Thirty to one, by the time
I placed my bet.

460
00:24:38,245 --> 00:24:40,972
Hmm, couldn't resist it, huh?

461
00:24:41,225 --> 00:24:43,545
Have a bit of a problem.

462
00:24:43,545 --> 00:24:46,417
So all that talk about Jerry's big heart,

463
00:24:46,417 --> 00:24:48,711
and how there's no stopping him.

464
00:24:48,711 --> 00:24:49,903
Just words?

465
00:24:49,903 --> 00:24:51,274
No!

466
00:24:51,274 --> 00:24:55,148
But why should all the other shlubs
make money off of Jerry and not us?

467
00:24:55,148 --> 00:24:56,687
So you did it for the both of you?

468
00:24:56,687 --> 00:24:59,083
Yeah. / Why are we gonna believe you?

469
00:24:59,083 --> 00:25:02,547
Because I did tell Jerry and it cost me.

470
00:25:03,603 --> 00:25:07,069
- Nervous about tomorrow?
- No.

471
00:25:07,069 --> 00:25:09,269
No?

472
00:25:09,834 --> 00:25:12,717
Well, not like tonight.

473
00:25:12,717 --> 00:25:14,705
What's so big about tonight?

474
00:25:15,179 --> 00:25:20,250
♪ Elton John
"Someone Saved My Life Tonight" ♪

475
00:25:34,655 --> 00:25:36,932
Well, what do you say?

476
00:25:40,701 --> 00:25:43,043
Jerry...

477
00:25:47,817 --> 00:25:51,080
Mo's gonna fall down
on the first round.

478
00:25:51,080 --> 00:25:53,281
You're gonna win.

479
00:25:53,281 --> 00:25:54,939
What?

480
00:25:54,939 --> 00:25:57,474
Are you joking me or not?

481
00:25:58,719 --> 00:26:02,198
We're gonna make some money.

482
00:26:07,131 --> 00:26:09,379
Are you saying you put a bet down?

483
00:26:09,379 --> 00:26:11,018
Baby...

484
00:26:11,018 --> 00:26:12,794
Just go along with it.

485
00:26:12,794 --> 00:26:15,633
There's nothing that you can do.

486
00:26:15,633 --> 00:26:16,886
It's all set, huh?

487
00:26:16,886 --> 00:26:20,173
Jerry, this is our chance.

488
00:26:20,173 --> 00:26:21,883
We can get out of this stinking
neighborhood.

489
00:26:21,883 --> 00:26:24,249
What, by being a bum?

490
00:26:24,249 --> 00:26:27,515
That's exactly what I'm trying not to be.

491
00:26:27,515 --> 00:26:31,429
I thought you believed
in what I was doing. / Jerry,

492
00:26:31,429 --> 00:26:35,558
we're stuck. And when we are
fifty we will still be stuck.

493
00:26:35,558 --> 00:26:37,423
We're not gonna get a break
like this again.

494
00:26:37,423 --> 00:26:40,670
We'll make our own breaks.

495
00:26:41,527 --> 00:26:42,736
You really believe that?

496
00:26:42,736 --> 00:26:45,178
That's why I want this fight.

497
00:26:45,178 --> 00:26:47,366
To prove it.

498
00:27:04,142 --> 00:27:07,314
I guess I should take that back.

499
00:27:15,319 --> 00:27:18,649
We see it all so different now.

500
00:27:27,417 --> 00:27:30,623
Hmm, short engagement.

501
00:27:31,667 --> 00:27:34,933
To make matters worse, I had to
go talk Frank Shavers what I'd done.

502
00:27:34,933 --> 00:27:36,398
Who's Shavers?

503
00:27:36,398 --> 00:27:39,106
From the old neighbohood
I worked in his bingo parlor.

504
00:27:39,106 --> 00:27:42,020
If anyone had a bet on this fix,
it was him.

505
00:27:42,020 --> 00:27:44,185
So you told him
that Jerry knew about it.

506
00:27:44,185 --> 00:27:46,962
And to take his bet back
before it was too late.

507
00:27:46,962 --> 00:27:48,546
What did he say?

508
00:27:48,546 --> 00:27:51,835
There is no taking bets back.

509
00:27:56,932 --> 00:27:58,965
So, Frank. You've been
big money on this fix,

510
00:27:58,965 --> 00:28:01,458
then Gina opens up her mouth to Jerry.

511
00:28:01,458 --> 00:28:03,215
I wasn't pleased.

512
00:28:03,215 --> 00:28:04,991
So did you retaliate?

513
00:28:04,991 --> 00:28:06,307
How would I have done that?

514
00:28:06,307 --> 00:28:10,039
How about paying the referee
1,500 bucks to not stop the fight.

515
00:28:10,039 --> 00:28:12,094
No matter how bad off Jerry was.

516
00:28:12,094 --> 00:28:13,714
Getting me what?

517
00:28:13,714 --> 00:28:16,091
Jerry ends up maimed or dead,

518
00:28:16,091 --> 00:28:18,451
The boxing world gets the message:

519
00:28:18,451 --> 00:28:20,478
Don't mess with Frank Shavers.

520
00:28:20,478 --> 00:28:24,533
Ha, ha, ha. I'm not a thug,
I'm a businessman.

521
00:28:24,533 --> 00:28:26,623
And it was a bad day at the office.

522
00:28:26,623 --> 00:28:28,757
So you never tampered with Sonny?

523
00:28:28,757 --> 00:28:31,149
I never suspected anyone had.

524
00:28:31,149 --> 00:28:33,239
Until now.

525
00:28:33,861 --> 00:28:35,720
We're listening.

526
00:28:35,720 --> 00:28:38,127
Jerry lasted fifteen rounds.

527
00:28:38,127 --> 00:28:40,333
That's incredible, really.

528
00:28:40,333 --> 00:28:42,412
But what's more incredible is,

529
00:28:42,412 --> 00:28:46,858
Only one person bet on
Jerry to do just said.

530
00:28:48,432 --> 00:28:50,969
There you go Frank.

531
00:29:00,723 --> 00:29:02,486
It finally hit ya, huh?

532
00:29:02,486 --> 00:29:04,365
What's that?

533
00:29:04,829 --> 00:29:09,995
Three years from now, Mo Bell may
be heavyweight champion of the world.

534
00:29:09,995 --> 00:29:12,607
That's what you're tangling with.

535
00:29:21,524 --> 00:29:26,441
There's no shame in knowing
when to walk away.

536
00:29:26,812 --> 00:29:28,323
No?

537
00:29:28,323 --> 00:29:30,945
It's the same in respect to Gina.

538
00:29:30,945 --> 00:29:33,173
Return the ring Jerry.

539
00:29:33,173 --> 00:29:35,714
Let my daughter be.

540
00:29:38,466 --> 00:29:41,350
Drink in the night before the fight.

541
00:29:41,670 --> 00:29:44,003
Put it down.

542
00:29:51,036 --> 00:29:54,025
Every reflex has to be right,
your mind clear.

543
00:29:54,025 --> 00:29:55,653
Father, it don't matter anymore.

544
00:29:55,653 --> 00:29:57,205
- What are you, freezing up?
- No!

545
00:29:57,205 --> 00:29:59,352
Well then, fight!

546
00:29:59,352 --> 00:30:03,488
Then you'll have tomorrow night
for the rest of your life!

547
00:30:05,027 --> 00:30:07,972
- You really think I can do it, father?
- Son.

548
00:30:07,972 --> 00:30:09,938
I got money on ya.

549
00:30:09,938 --> 00:30:11,814
You too, father?

550
00:30:12,216 --> 00:30:13,552
You bet on the fight?

551
00:30:13,552 --> 00:30:16,073
Now I need you in that ring.

552
00:30:17,233 --> 00:30:18,862
Father... / Son.

553
00:30:18,862 --> 00:30:22,099
I've raised you from a pup.

554
00:30:22,099 --> 00:30:26,578
If you won't do it for yourself,
do it for me.

555
00:30:33,074 --> 00:30:35,706
So, father needs Jerry to
go the distance.

556
00:30:35,706 --> 00:30:38,517
That night, seized Jerry's wobbly.

557
00:30:38,517 --> 00:30:40,785
I didn't stick around but,

558
00:30:40,785 --> 00:30:44,528
Father was huddled up
with Sonny when I left.

559
00:30:44,528 --> 00:30:47,380
Maybe father bought
some insurance from him.

560
00:30:47,380 --> 00:30:51,095
Made sure his 'pup'
got to the finish line.

561
00:30:53,023 --> 00:30:55,113
Putting money on Jerry not to win,

562
00:30:55,113 --> 00:30:57,254
but to make it fifteen rounds?

563
00:30:57,254 --> 00:30:59,310
That's a pretty specific bet, father.

564
00:30:59,310 --> 00:31:01,334
That's because Jerry set
that goal for himself.

565
00:31:01,334 --> 00:31:02,450
I thought he could make it.

566
00:31:02,450 --> 00:31:04,689
And your winnings must've been sweet.

567
00:31:04,689 --> 00:31:06,864
I've threw in the towel for Pete's sake.

568
00:31:06,864 --> 00:31:09,491
Yeah. With twenty seconds remaining.

569
00:31:09,491 --> 00:31:12,189
Because of what I saw in his eyes.
Jerry always looked bad.

570
00:31:12,189 --> 00:31:14,268
But this time I could see
he was cooked.

571
00:31:14,268 --> 00:31:18,949
Or maybe throwing that towel
was just an act. Huh, father?

572
00:31:18,949 --> 00:31:20,022
Look.

573
00:31:20,022 --> 00:31:23,439
I can't force you two to believe me.

574
00:31:23,719 --> 00:31:25,721
Did you know the fight was fixed?

575
00:31:25,721 --> 00:31:26,920
Fixed?

576
00:31:26,920 --> 00:31:29,163
Mo made a deal to let Jerry
to win in the first round.

577
00:31:29,163 --> 00:31:31,446
And Jerry knew about it.

578
00:31:31,446 --> 00:31:32,789
No kidding?

579
00:31:32,789 --> 00:31:35,086
But didn't wanna go along with it.

580
00:31:35,086 --> 00:31:37,572
I wouldn't think he would.

581
00:31:37,805 --> 00:31:39,608
And if so, that explains why...

582
00:31:39,608 --> 00:31:40,831
Why what?

583
00:31:40,831 --> 00:31:43,301
That's why round one.

584
00:31:57,009 --> 00:31:58,792
He's been standing around for two minutes!

585
00:31:58,792 --> 00:32:01,212
- What the hell's going in out there?
- C'mon! C'mon!

586
00:32:01,212 --> 00:32:02,969
C'mon, hit me!

587
00:32:03,872 --> 00:32:06,219
Oh, wonderful. The boo birds.

588
00:32:07,251 --> 00:32:08,885
C'mon, throw him a punch.

589
00:32:08,885 --> 00:32:09,664
C'mon!

590
00:32:09,664 --> 00:32:11,440
Show me something, chump!

591
00:32:11,440 --> 00:32:14,886
- You know what, Mo...
- Don't talk! C'mon.

592
00:32:16,006 --> 00:32:17,340
C'mon!

593
